{
  "stem": "21788.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I must tell you, at that time, we were absolutely warned-- this during the Hitler period-- not to wear our best clothes when we went to the High Holiday services.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By the Jewish rabbis.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Don't make a scene.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Don't congregate in front of the synagogue in a great big group.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Be inconspicuous.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Don't flaunt it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, don't go in groups, kind of file in, and go out, and go home, and don't talk in front of the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Interestingly enough the synagogues, most of the synagogues in Germany where not facing the street.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You usually had to go through an apartment house in the front, through a gate, and then the second [NON-ENGLISH], the second section of the house, that's where the synagogue was.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, the big one, Oranienburger Strasse.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is the one that had the gold dome.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is the one that, of course, was burned, and this is the one also that got bombed during the bombings of Berlin.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this is the one that is now, I understand, completely restored by the Berlin government.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Kristallnacht?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, I do remember that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The reason I remember it is, we lived at that time at Bruckenstrasse facing the front, and right across the street from us where two businesses, one of them was a bakery.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The bakery, [GERMAN]-- and I have-- could I say and aside right here?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember because it was a bakery, and we got our hard rolls there every morning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We also, when we baked cakes, we mixed the cakes at home, then took the cake and went over there and had it baked in the oven.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the way the fashion was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I went back in 1993, I went back to Bruckenstrasse.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Across the street was still the bakery.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
